Running the first spider in Pycharm:


import scrapy

class PostsSpiders(scrapy.Spider):
   name = "posts"
   start_urls = [
       'http://www.discipleshiplibrary.com/index.php'
   ]

   def parse(self, response):
       title = response.css('title::text').extract()
       yield {'titletext': title}



There is a period of time that I could not figure out why ‘scrapy’ is not able to be recognized as an internal or external command until it got fixed finally after a few days.
